Python package for OCRe

* Git repo: https://github.com/bitsofparag/ocre
* Documentation: https://github.com/bitsofparag/ocre/docs
* Free software: MIT

Introduction
------------

A simple image-processing library for reading spreadsheets

Setup and Usage
---------------

Once you are in the project root:

1. `pip install -r requirements.txt -r requirements-dev.txt`

2. `docker pull tesseractshadow/tesseract4re`

3. `docker build -t my_ocr:latest .`

4. You can invoke the program by executing the docker command:

   `docker run -it --rm -v $PWD:/usr/src/my_ocr my_ocr:latest python3 -m my_ocr.main`

5. Alternately, you can work in development mode from inside the docker container by mounting the source code:

   `docker run -it --rm -v $PWD:/usr/src/my_ocr my_ocr:latest bash`

